THIS LEASE, made and entered into this
day of
March, 1927, by and between MILLS ESTATE INCORPORATED, a
corporation duly organized and existing under and by virtue of
the laws of the State of California, and hereinafter called the
"lessor", and CITY AND COUNTY OF SAN FRANCISCO, a municipal
corporation, hereinafter called the "lessee".
WINESSETH:
That the lessor has leased, demised and let, and does by
these presents hereby lease, demise and let unto the lessee, all
of that certain real property situate in the County of San Mateo,
State of California, described as follows, to-wit:
B portion of Sections 34
and
3,
35,
Township
S• R• 5W.,
and Sections 2 and
3, Town-
ship 4, S• R• 5 W•, M. D. B. & M•
and containing an area of one hundred
and
fifty (150) acres more
or less, the location and dimensions of said
property being more
definitely shown on the print hereto attached, marked "Exhibit
A", and made a part of this lease.
TO HAVE AND TO HOLD the same unto the said lessee for the
term of three (3) years from the 15th day of March, 1927, at the
annual rental of Fifteen Hundred ($1500) Dollars, payable in
advance on the 15th day of March of each year during the said
term. That the lessee agrees to pay the rental hereinbefore re-
served, at the time and in the manner hereinbefore set forth, and
to have, hold, use and enjoy said premises upon the terns and
conditions herein contained.
1.
That the lessee shall have the right to construct and
maintain a water pipe line and water tank on the lands belonging
to the lessor and adjacent on the west to the premises herein
demised,
it being the intention of the lessee to connect the said
water
tank and pipe line with
the mains of the Spring Valley Water
Company or such other water company as may be most convenient
for the said lessee for the purpose of supplying water for all
